A Glimpse into History
Founded in 1945, the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove boasts a legacy steeped in tradition and academic prowess. It emerged as a pioneering institution in the post-war era, dedicated to fostering medical excellence and serving the healthcare needs of the community. Over the decades, it has evolved into a renowned center of learning, attracting students and scholars from across the globe.

